==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Independence
<hw>In`de*pend"ence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>ind⟦eacute⟧pendance</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The state or quality of being independent; freedom
from dependence; exemption from reliance on, or control by, others;
self-subsistence or maintenance; direction of one's own affairs without
interference.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let fortune do her worst, . . . as long as she never makes us lose
our honesty and our <qex>independence</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Sufficient means for a comfortable
livelihood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Declaration of Independence</b></col> <fld>(Amer.
Hist.)</fld>, <cd>the declaration of the Congress of the Thirteen United
States of America, on the 4th of July, 1776, by which they formally
declared that these colonies were free and independent States, not
subject to the government of Great Britain.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Independence Day</ent>⟦br⟧
